{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"virid-trench-stone","description":"# WS6 — Gerrit LLM-Review voter + dogfood\n\n## Why\nThe dogfood success criterion: rebar's own changes are reviewed and gated end-to-end through Gerrit's `LLM-Review` label. This is the only workstream gated on external infra (the AWS Gerrit + rebar MCP provisioning epic d251-05e1-eb55-43b2, OPEN).\n\n## What\n- On `patchset-created`, run the four-pass code-review gate over the change and vote `LLM-Review` via Gerrit REST; the deterministic block/advisory outcome maps to the label.\n- Prove end-to-end: at least one real rebar change reviewed + gated on the AWS/Gerrit environment.\n\n## Scope\n- The Gerrit voter integration (event wiring + REST vote) in the rebar MCP server.\n- OUT OF SCOPE: the capability itself (WS1-WS5); the CI \"Verified\" second vote (epic 1fa8).\n\n## Dependencies\n- BLOCKED ON d251-05e1-eb55-43b2 (AWS Gerrit + rebar MCP provisioning). The epic-level b744<-d251 blocker already enforces this; this story cannot complete until d251 lands.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] On patchset-created, the gate reviews the change, runs the four passes, and votes `LLM-Review` via REST; block/advisory maps to the label value.\n- [ ] Dogfood proof: at least one real rebar change is reviewed + gated end-to-end on the AWS/Gerrit environment (record the change URL + the resulting vote on this ticket).\n","id":"4119-1a4f-19ff-4cfa","parent_id":"b744-4fb9-2d05-4b49","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS6: Gerrit LLM-Review voter + dogfood (gated on d251)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782620594113128001,"uuid":"761b3ff4-bbad-44c0-ba90-cfed00dc92f7"}